annotationA: DnaJ homolog subfamily C member 5 homolog; Cysteine string protein (Csp) is a synaptic vesicle-associated co-chaperone of Hsc70 that is vital for presynaptic proteostasis and maintenance of synaptic function. Csp protein substrates include SNARE proteins and shi, which mediate synaptic vesicle exo- and endocytosis respectively
annotationB: DHX15 ortholog, isoform A; ATP binding; ATP-dependent helicase activity; ATP-dependent RNA helicase activity; nucleic acid binding; RNA helicase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: mRNA splicing, via spliceosome; neurogenesis
